The meeting will begin at 9 a.m. The presiding officer, who will be a representative of OSHA's Directorate of Safety
Standards Programs, will have the necessary authority to regulate the conduct of the meeting.
OSHA requests that any person wishing to make oral presentations notify OSHA in advance. The notice should identify
